"Agent Skills 管理说明正文" = "When to use\n• Package reusable prompts, workflows, or domain knowledge as skills the model can call with use_skill.\n• Keep imported skills, enablement, and SKILL.md content in one place.\n\nRecommended flow\n1. Add a skill by pasting SKILL.md, importing a local file, or importing from GitHub.\n2. Confirm the skill is enabled.\n3. Turn on “Expose Agent Skills to model”.\n4. Ask in chat as usual; the model can call use_skill when the skill is relevant.\n\nSKILL.md format\n• Frontmatter can declare name, description, when_to_use, and related fields.\n• If a directory or repository omits name, the folder name is used; if description is omitted, the first body paragraph is used.\n• The body can contain instructions, parameters, examples, and other Markdown content.\n\nTroubleshooting\n• If the model does not call a skill, check the global switch and the individual enabled state.\n• If import fails, verify the repository or file, or paste SKILL.md manually.";
"MCP 工具箱说明正文" = "When to use\n• Connect external service capabilities to chat, such as retrieval, tool execution, or resource reading.\n• Diagnose why a tool is not available or not being called.\n\nRecommended flow\n1. Add or edit an MCP Server and confirm it connects.\n2. Turn on “Expose MCP tools to model”.\n3. Check the connection overview and published capabilities.\n4. Review individual tools, enabled state, and approval policy.\n\nKey settings\n• Auto-approve countdown controls how long approval waits before allowing a call.\n• Tool enablement decides whether a specific tool is visible to the model.\n• Approval policy can allow, deny, or ask every time.\n\nTroubleshooting\n• If a tool is not called, check the global switch, enabled state, approval policy, and session isolation.\n• If a call fails, inspect active calls, governance logs, and the latest response.";
"世界书说明正文" = "What it does\n• Worldbooks inject context by rules when a message is sent.\n• They are static rule knowledge and do not write into the memory system.\n\nRecommended flow\n1. Import a worldbook from JSON, PNG, or URL.\n2. Bind the needed worldbooks to the current session.\n3. Enable isolation only when the session should send just prompts and worldbook context.\n\nKey status\n• Binding count shows how many worldbooks are bound to the session.\n• Enabled entries show how dense each worldbook is.\n• Isolation blocks memory, MCP, Shortcuts, and other external tool context for that session.\n\nTips\n• For large worldbooks, keep disabled entries pruned so context stays focused.\n• After import, check the latest report for failed entries and conflicts.\n• Export important worldbooks regularly as backups.";
"为模型提供自定义技能，通过 use_skill 在聊天中按需调用。" = "Provide custom skills to the model and call them on demand in chat through use_skill.";
"图片相册说明正文" = "What appears here\n• Images returned by assistant messages in the current session.\n• These are chat results, not a separate image generation workspace.\n\nWhat you can do\n• Open an image to view it larger and inspect its prompt context when available.\n• Save or share images from the action menu.\n• Deleting an image removes the local image reference from that message.\n\nTips\n• To keep generating or editing images, return to chat and describe the change.\n• To organize older results, switch to the relevant session first.";
"在手表端查看并管理已同步的快捷指令工具。" = "View and manage synced Shortcut tools on Apple Watch.";
"在手表端查看服务器状态、工具能力和治理日志。" = "Consultez sur Apple Watch l’état des serveurs, les capacités d’outils et les journaux de gouvernance.";
"字体样式优先级说明正文" = "Recommended flow\n1. Import the font files you want to use.\n2. Choose a style slot, such as body, italic, bold, or code.\n3. Reorder fonts so the preferred one is higher.\n4. Add missing fonts to the current slot when needed.\n5. Removing a font from a slot does not delete the font file.\n\nRules\n• Each style slot has its own priority chain.\n• The same font can appear in multiple slots.\n• If all fonts in a slot are unavailable, the app falls back to the system font.";
"当前对话模型不支持图片输入时，用于先把图片识别为文字；手表端默认不选择。" = "When the current chat model does not support image input, use this to recognize images as text first; no default is selected on watchOS.";
"快捷指令工具箱说明正文" = "When to use\n• Let the model call iOS Shortcuts during chat for automation tasks.\n• Manage import sources, enabled state, run mode, and approval behavior in one place.\n\nRecommended flow\n1. Import tools on iPhone with the official shortcut or clipboard manifest.\n2. Confirm the tool list has synced to Apple Watch if you use watchOS.\n3. Turn on “Expose shortcut tools to model”.\n4. Review each tool description, enabled state, run mode, and approval countdown.\n\nImport modes\n• Light import only reads names and is good for quick setup.\n• Deep import tries to parse iCloud shares and generate descriptions; if it fails, it falls back to links only.\n\nTroubleshooting\n• If a tool is not called, check the global switch and the individual enabled state.\n• If URL Scheme or urlshim navigation fails, import again from the clipboard manifest.";
"拓展功能说明正文" = "What this page is for\n• Manage advanced capabilities that are outside the core chat flow.\n• Jump quickly into maintenance, import, debugging, voice, and tool integration pages.\n\nHow to choose\n• Memory System / Worldbook manage long-term context and rule knowledge.\n• MCP / Shortcuts / Agent Skills expose external capabilities or reusable skills to the model.\n• Storage Management / Remote File Access help with cleanup and troubleshooting.\n\nTips\n• Enable advanced features as needed so the main chat flow stays focused.\n• Back up important data before imports, restores, or cleanup.";
"按关键词规则注入上下文，不会写入记忆系统。" = "Injects context by keyword rules without writing to memory.";
"按槽位管理字体顺序，越靠上优先级越高。" = "Manage font order by slot; higher entries have higher priority.";
"用于图片生成，也可在图片生成功能中修改。" = "Used for image generation; can also be changed in Image Generation.";
"用于文字转语音，也可在 TTS 设置中修改。" = "Used for text-to-speech; can also be changed in TTS Settings.";
"用于记忆嵌入，也可在记忆库管理中修改。" = "Used for memory embeddings; can also be changed in Memory Library Management.";
"用于语音转文字，也可在偏好设置中修改。" = "Used for speech-to-text; can also be changed in Preferences.";
"让 AI 持续理解你的长期偏好和上下文。" = "Let AI continuously understand your long-term preferences and context.";
"记忆检索说明正文" = "Retrieval count (Top K)\n• When greater than 0, the app retrieves the most relevant memories for the current message.\n• When set to 0, vector retrieval is skipped and all active memory text is sent directly.\n• The default value is 3.\n\nActive retrieval\n• When enabled, the search_memory tool is exposed to AI.\n• AI can actively search by vector or keyword and choose how many results to return.\n• Active retrieval may reduce context cache hits.\n\nSend update time\n• When enabled, each memory includes its last update time.\n• When disabled, only memory content is sent.";
"记忆系统说明正文" = "What it does\n• The memory system retrieves historical information before replies, helping the model connect past preferences and context.\n• Unlike Worldbook, memory is dynamic knowledge that can be accumulated, read, and written.\n\nKey switches\n• Enable Memory is the global switch. When off, the app neither retrieves nor writes new memories.\n• Allow writing new memories only controls writing; existing memories can still be read.\n\nRecommended use\n1. Turn on the global switch first and observe whether replies fit long-term preferences better.\n2. If noisy memories are a concern, disable writing and keep reading only.\n3. Clean low-quality or outdated memories in Memory Library regularly.";
